      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ENGELKE ROAD (1) stuck on well last time to finish one length back in second (29.65) at Sandown in a Grade 4/5 over 515m. Has a strong record out of this box with three wins and a minor placing from six starts. Must come into calculations. MOTOR CITY ROSSI (7) claimed an on-pace win two back then gave a start but got home into the frame when third at Sandown (30.01). Expected to be in this for a long way. HIS SPECIAL (5) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished in the minors latest when third (33.32) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Expecting another good run. PARABOLA (2) is worth consideration.",
